******
[2] USA, Louisiana
Date: Fri 17 Feb 2017
Source: Thoroughbred Daily News [edited]
http://www.thoroughbreddailynews.com/quarantine-restrictions-lifted-at-fair-grounds/


The final horses remaining in the testing protocols for the Equine Herpes Virus (EHV-1) outbreak at Fair Grounds have returned 2 negative tests and have been released back into the general horse population on the backstretch.

Since the 1st case of EHV-1 was reported [Mon 26 Dec 2016] any horse testing positive was promptly isolated under the protocols set forth by the Louisiana Department of Agriculture and Forestry and then required after 14 days to return 2 negative tests, not less than 72 hours apart, before being permitted back into the general horse population.

"The Louisiana Department of Agriculture and Forestry (LDAF), USDA Veterinary Services and the Louisiana Racing Commission responded to an EHV-1 outbreak at the New Orleans Fair Grounds Race Track on [Mon 26 Dec 2016]," said State Veterinarian Brent Robbins, D.V.M. "On [Tue 14 Feb 2017], the last horse in isolation tested negative and was released after a prescribed observation period. We at the LDAF extend our appreciation to all agencies involved as well as horse owners, trainers and officials at the New Orleans Fair Grounds for their cooperation and understanding in dealing with this outbreak."

As of [Wed 15 Feb 2017] no horses remain in the EHV-1 testing protocols at Fair Grounds and all quarantine restrictions have been lifted by the Louisiana Department of Agriculture and Forestry.

