[Current EHV-1 vaccines can reduce viral shedding but are not licensed to protect against the neurologic form of the disease. It is surely difficult but it seems someone should be working on a vaccine for the neurological form of this disease. Using the current vaccine does not necessarily guarantee your animal may not get the neurological form of the disease. However, strict disinfecting of trailers, water buckets, grooming tools, halters, lead lines, etc may be helpful in preventing this disease. Additionally disinfecting feed pans/bins may be especially important if they are supplied by the facility where the horse is being taken for a race or show, or any type of travel.

We need to celebrate the positive outcomes of any disease. This disease hit the Louisiana race track particularly hard and threatened to wipe out their entire racing season. It's great to hear they have a clean bill of health. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4849258,260, https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4849258,221.]
